bbb-plugin-rtt-monitor (0.1.0-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Scrolling time axis: x-axis ticks are now anchored to wall-clock
    minute boundaries and slide left as time advances — the tick mark and
    its label move together and scroll off the left edge — instead of
    sitting at fixed pixel positions while only their labels change. Tick
    spacing picks the smallest "nice" minute step (1/2/5/10/15/30/60) that
    fits the plot width.

 -- Brent Baccala <cosine@freesoft.org>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 19:16:27 -0400

bbb-plugin-rtt-monitor (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release. Moderator-only live per-user connection-RTT
    monitor for BigBlueButton v3.0. Launcher in the options ("...")
    menu (moderators only); a movable floating window plots every
    participant's networkRttInMs over a rolling window (default
    10 min) as a per-user scatter on a log axis with the BBB
    warning/danger/critical thresholds drawn in. Data comes from a
    custom subscription on the user_connectionStatusHistory GraphQL
    view, joined with the user relationship for name/role; Hasura
    permissions scope rows to all meeting users for a moderator and
    own-rows-only for a viewer. The panel keeps its own rolling
    client-side buffer so the window grows past the server's
    last-N-samples cap and degrades gracefully when little history
    exists.

 -- Brent Baccala <cosine@freesoft.org>  Wed, 18 Jun 2026 19:00:00 +0000
